Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces and place in a #medium pot{}
with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a
boil and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Reserve 1⁄2 cup
potato cooking liquid, then drain. Return potatoes to pot and mash
with half the @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and @butter{1%TBSP} until
smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid
as needed. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep covered off
heat until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced),
separating whites from greens. Trim, peel, and quarter @carrots{6%ounce}(peeled and quartered)
lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into quarter-moons.

Open package of @ground turkey{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

> Swap in beef or chicken for turkey. Cook as instructed, breaking up meat
> into pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add turkey, scallion whites, carrots, and half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon};
season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until turkey is
browned and nearly cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} and @butter{1%TBSP}. Cook, stirring
constantly, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Sprinkle @flour{1%tablespoon} evenly over turkey mixture; stir to combine.

Add @water{1%cup}, @peas{4%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and
remaining sour cream; cook, whisking constantly, until gravy has thickened
and turkey is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} (if gravy seems too thick,
add more water 1 TBSP at a time). Taste and season with salt and
pepper if desired.

Divide sour cream mashed potatoes between shallow #bowls{}. Top with
crustless turkey pot pie and garnish with scallion greens. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.